  script_tag(name:"insight", value:"Wojciech Regula discovered that Freeplane, a program for working with mind maps, was affected by a XML External Entity (XXE) vulnerability in its mindmap loader that could compromise a user's machine by opening a specially crafted mind map file.

For Debian 7 Wheezy, these problems have been fixed in version 1.1.3-2+deb7u1.

We recommend that you upgrade your freeplane packages.

